Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips. Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the chips cook, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1} and halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}. Peel the @garlic clove{1}, pop it into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. When ~{10%minutes} of cooking time remain for the chips, pop the garlic parcel into the oven and roast until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}. Remove from the oven once roasted and set aside to cool.

Meanwhile, put the @cornflour{20%g} and @Central American style spice mix{1} into a large #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix to combine. Cut the @British chicken thighs{2} lengthways into 2cm wide strips. Add the chicken strips to the bowl and turn them over in the spiced cornflour mix to coat well.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Put a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, then reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} total. Turn every 2-3 mins and adjust the heat as necessary. Discard any cornflour left in the bowl. Once cooked, remove from the heat and place the chicken onto #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When everything is nearly ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{4} onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Meanwhile, put the sliced baby gem and tomatoes into a medium bowl. Pour over the @French dressing{1}, then toss well to coat. Remove the roasted garlic from the foil, pop it into a small bowl, then mash with a #fork{}. Add the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} to the garlic and stir to combine.

To assemble your wraps, lay the warmed tortillas on your plates (2 per person). Spread a spoonful of garlic mayo on each, then top with some of the dressed salad, fried chicken strips and a sprinkle of grated cheese. Roll up the wraps, then plate up the chips and any remaining salad alongside. Serve with the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} on the side for dipping. Enjoy!